255
00:11:24,880 --> 00:11:26,320
 Like, this is great.

256
00:11:26,320 --> 00:11:28,760
 They're looking up Zillow going, we can afford this.

257
00:11:28,760 --> 00:11:30,000
 Like, this is awesome.

258
00:11:30,000 --> 00:11:31,040
 Oh, there's a coffee shop here.

259
00:11:31,040 --> 00:11:32,360
 It's walking distance to target.

260
00:11:32,360 --> 00:11:34,140
 This is a main walking trail.

261
00:11:34,140 --> 00:11:35,120
 They start dating.

262
00:11:35,120 --> 00:11:36,960
 They're like, well, I just got in community.

263
00:11:36,960 --> 00:11:38,040
 I don't want to leave her.

264
00:11:38,040 --> 00:11:39,760
 They're like settled.

265
00:11:39,760 --> 00:11:41,600
 They're settled in Shinar.

266
00:11:41,600 --> 00:11:44,300
 And then it says in verse three, look in verse three.

267
00:11:44,300 --> 00:11:46,560
 It says, and they said to one another,

268
00:11:46,560 --> 00:11:51,320
 come, let us make bricks and burn them thoroughly.

269
00:11:51,320 --> 00:11:54,840
 And they had brick for stone and bitumen for mortar.

270
00:11:54,840 --> 00:11:56,860
 So they gather up at the coffee shop

271
00:11:56,860 --> 00:11:57,840
 and they're having group think.

272
00:11:57,840 --> 00:12:00,040
 They're like, guys, what do we do now?

273
00:12:00,040 --> 00:12:02,280
 Like, we're just chilling, paying our mortgage.

274
00:12:02,280 --> 00:12:03,800
 We're drinking our latte.

275
00:12:03,800 --> 00:12:06,880
 And they go, oh, there's that cunning edge technology.

276
00:12:06,880 --> 00:12:11,240
 Brick, which is hardened clay, and bitumen,

277
00:12:11,240 --> 00:12:14,880
 which is like waterproof mortar.

278
00:12:14,880 --> 00:12:16,760
 It's adhesive.

279
00:12:16,760 --> 00:12:18,320
 And they say, if we put those together,

280
00:12:18,320 --> 00:12:20,280
 we can build something great.

281
00:12:20,280 --> 00:12:22,800
 And then look what they build, verse four.

282
00:12:22,800 --> 00:12:26,480
 Then they said, come, let us build ourselves a city

283
00:12:26,480 --> 00:12:29,200
 and a tower with its top in the heavens.

284
00:12:29,200 --> 00:12:31,960
 And let us make a name for ourselves,

285
00:12:31,960 --> 00:12:35,960
 lest we be dispersed over the face of the whole earth.

286
00:12:35,960 --> 00:12:39,560
 So they say, let's make a city and a tower to the heavens

287
00:12:39,560 --> 00:12:41,840
 and let's make a name for ourselves.

288
00:12:41,840 --> 00:12:42,680
 And that'll be awesome.

289
00:12:42,680 --> 00:12:45,900
 And you wonder, we all know like, guys, don't do that.

290
00:12:45,900 --> 00:12:47,080
 But why?

291
00:12:47,080 --> 00:12:48,560
 Why?

292
00:12:48,560 --> 00:12:51,360
 So interesting, when you think about what they're building,

293
00:12:51,360 --> 00:12:56,360
 they're building a waterproof tower that goes into heaven.

294
00:12:57,200 --> 00:12:59,640
 Now think about what we talked about last week,

295
00:12:59,640 --> 00:13:01,480
 Noah and the flood.

296
00:13:01,480 --> 00:13:04,300
 What did God just do to the whole earth?

297
00:13:04,300 --> 00:13:05,640
 He flooded it.

298
00:13:05,640 --> 00:13:07,920
 And so they're sitting around in Shinar,

299
00:13:07,920 --> 00:13:10,840
 drinking their lattes going, oh, I got an idea.

300
00:13:10,840 --> 00:13:14,620
 What if we build a waterproof tower straight up to God?

301
00:13:14,620 --> 00:13:18,560
 We're not gonna focus on the fact that He promised

302
00:13:18,560 --> 00:13:20,680
 that would never happen again.

303
00:13:20,680 --> 00:13:23,640
 We're not gonna focus on the fact that it was actually

304
00:13:23,640 --> 00:13:25,280
 due to the wickedness of man.

305
00:13:25,280 --> 00:13:27,440
 No, no, no, we're gonna build this tower

306
00:13:27,440 --> 00:13:29,100
 so we don't need God.

307
00:13:29,100 --> 00:13:30,920
 We don't need to focus on His promises.

308
00:13:30,920 --> 00:13:33,920
 We don't need to freak out about His threats.

309
00:13:33,920 --> 00:13:35,780
 We can be our own God.

310
00:13:35,780 --> 00:13:37,320
 That's what this is about.

311
00:13:37,320 --> 00:13:41,040
 And they begin to build this tower up to heaven.

312
00:13:41,040 --> 00:13:43,760
 Now I want us to think, pause here for a second.

313
00:13:43,760 --> 00:13:46,260
 Where are we doing this today?

314
00:13:46,260 --> 00:13:50,720
 Now it's easy to think of things like AI, right?

315
00:13:50,720 --> 00:13:52,840
 I mean, AI is a great example

316
00:13:52,840 --> 00:13:54,680
 because AI is kind of this idea of,

317
00:13:54,680 --> 00:13:56,080
 oh God, we don't really need you.

318
00:13:56,080 --> 00:13:57,560
 We're just gonna create you.

319
00:13:57,560 --> 00:14:00,120
 We're just gonna make somebody who can do everything you do.

320
00:14:00,120 --> 00:14:01,840
 And this could be a sermon on AI,

321
00:14:01,840 --> 00:14:06,840
 but I think God doesn't care so much about the tower.

322
00:14:06,840 --> 00:14:11,040
 I don't think God cares so much about the technology.

323
00:14:11,040 --> 00:14:14,440
 I think what God cares about is their mindset

324
00:14:14,440 --> 00:14:16,480
 behind why they're building it.

325
00:14:16,480 --> 00:14:19,680
 You see it in the second half of verse four.

326
00:14:19,680 --> 00:14:22,320
 That we may make a name for ourselves

327
00:14:22,320 --> 00:14:25,640
 lest we be dispersed over the face of the earth.

328
00:14:25,640 --> 00:14:27,600
 This is the motivation that God goes,

329
00:14:27,600 --> 00:14:29,160
 I got to deal with that.

330
00:14:29,160 --> 00:14:30,040
 So what does he do next?

331
00:14:30,040 --> 00:14:31,240
 Let's look at verse five.

332
00:14:31,240 --> 00:14:34,360
 Verse five, he says, it says,

333
00:14:34,360 --> 00:14:38,240
 "And the Lord came down to see the city and the tower

334
00:14:38,240 --> 00:14:40,560
 with which the children of man had built."

335
00:14:40,560 --> 00:14:43,200
 I love this because they build this tower.

336
00:14:43,200 --> 00:14:44,560
 They're like, we're gonna build a tower.

337
00:14:44,560 --> 00:14:46,080
 It's gonna go into the heavens.

338
00:14:46,080 --> 00:14:48,200
 And then verse five goes, "And God had to come down."

339
00:14:48,200 --> 00:14:49,920
 It's like, what's that amp pile down there?

340
00:14:49,920 --> 00:14:52,520
 You know, oh, they're building a tower.

341
00:14:52,520 --> 00:14:54,000
 Come Michael, check it out.

342
00:14:54,000 --> 00:14:55,000
 That's amazing.

343
00:14:55,000 --> 00:14:57,120
 Like God sees everything.

344
00:14:57,120 --> 00:14:58,160
 Is he saying he's blind?

345
00:14:58,160 --> 00:15:00,160
 No, it's irony.

346
00:15:00,160 --> 00:15:02,320
 It's like, God, they think they're getting to heaven.

347
00:15:02,320 --> 00:15:04,160
 God has to come down to them.

348
00:15:04,160 --> 00:15:05,600
 Look at verse six.

349
00:15:05,600 --> 00:15:08,960
 It says, "And the Lord said, 'Behold, they are one people.

350
00:15:08,960 --> 00:15:10,800
 They all have one language.

351
00:15:10,800 --> 00:15:13,720
 And this is only the beginning of what they will do.

352
00:15:13,720 --> 00:15:16,200
 And nothing that they propose to do

353
00:15:16,200 --> 00:15:18,840
 will now be impossible for them.'"

354
00:15:18,840 --> 00:15:22,240
 God looks down and he sees one people and one language.

355
00:15:22,240 --> 00:15:24,400
 And they're together and they're ambitious,

356
00:15:24,400 --> 00:15:27,400
 but they're building towards sin.

357
00:15:27,400 --> 00:15:30,920
 Their motivation is anti-God, not for God.

358
00:15:30,920 --> 00:15:34,680
 It made me think of teenagers.

359
00:15:34,680 --> 00:15:36,240
 Like I was a youth pastor for a number of years.

360
00:15:36,240 --> 00:15:41,240
 It's amazing how creative teenagers are

361
00:15:41,240 --> 00:15:42,880
 when it comes to sin.

362
00:15:42,880 --> 00:15:44,600
 I was thinking back when I was in high school,

363
00:15:44,600 --> 00:15:47,880
 like the laziest dude ever could be sitting in classes,

364
00:15:47,880 --> 00:15:48,760
 doing nothing.

365
00:15:48,760 --> 00:15:49,840
 Then the teacher goes out

366
00:15:49,840 --> 00:15:52,240
 and he sees the answers on the table.

367
00:15:52,240 --> 00:15:54,680
 And all of a sudden he's Tom Cruise from "Mission Impossible"

368
00:15:54,680 --> 00:15:56,720
 scaling walls, doing Morse code to his friends.

369
00:15:56,720 --> 00:15:58,120
 Like, we gotta get those answers

370
00:15:58,120 --> 00:16:00,480
 so I don't have to work, right?

371
00:16:00,480 --> 00:16:02,040
 Some of us in the midst of...

372
00:16:02,040 --> 00:16:03,840
 You have no ambition in your life

373
00:16:03,840 --> 00:16:06,120
 until it's hiding yourself in your sin.

374
00:16:06,120 --> 00:16:09,000
 You become incredibly creative.

375
00:16:09,000 --> 00:16:11,960
 You're amazing at working things behind the scenes

376
00:16:11,960 --> 00:16:13,280
 to make sure no one catches you.

377
00:16:13,280 --> 00:16:14,600
 And this is like them.

378
00:16:14,600 --> 00:16:15,920
 This is like them.

379
00:16:15,920 --> 00:16:18,080
 So is God threatened by this?

380
00:16:18,080 --> 00:16:20,240
 Is God going, "Oh no, he's the teacher walking back in.

381
00:16:20,240 --> 00:16:21,120
 "How could you?

382
00:16:21,120 --> 00:16:22,120
 "You stole the answers.

383
00:16:22,120 --> 00:16:23,000
 "What's going on?"

384
00:16:23,000 --> 00:16:24,760
 Is that what's happening?

385
00:16:24,760 --> 00:16:27,280
 No, he's not threatened by their ambition.

386
00:16:27,280 --> 00:16:31,680
 He recognizes the havoc that it can wreak on them

387
00:16:31,680 --> 00:16:33,800
 and society if left unchecked.

388
00:16:33,800 --> 00:16:34,640
 So what does he do?

389
00:16:34,640 --> 00:16:36,200
 Verse seven.

390
00:16:36,200 --> 00:16:39,080
 Verse seven, he says, "Come, let us,"

391
00:16:39,080 --> 00:16:42,040
 little nod to the Trinity, to the divine counsel,

392
00:16:42,040 --> 00:16:46,320
 "Let us go down there and confuse their language

393
00:16:46,320 --> 00:16:49,520
 "so that they may not understand one another's speech.

394
00:16:49,520 --> 00:16:53,040
 "So the Lord dispersed them over the face of all the earth

395
00:16:53,040 --> 00:16:55,400
 "and they left off building the city."

396
00:16:55,400 --> 00:16:59,640
 So here God says, "Come, let us, let us go down,

397
00:16:59,640 --> 00:17:02,280
 "confuse their language so they can't understand."

398
00:17:02,280 --> 00:17:06,680
 This is judgment, divine judgment on human beings.

399
00:17:06,680 --> 00:17:08,760
 They're gonna come together and do this?

400
00:17:08,760 --> 00:17:10,680
 Against my name, I'm gonna judge them.

401
00:17:10,680 --> 00:17:14,360
 And then it says, "So the Lord dispersed them

402
00:17:14,360 --> 00:17:16,240
 "over the earth."

403
00:17:16,240 --> 00:17:20,120
 He did the very thing that they feared in verse four.

404
00:17:20,120 --> 00:17:21,060
 Remember in verse four, they said,

405
00:17:21,060 --> 00:17:23,440
 "Oh, let's build this to heaven, make a great name

406
00:17:23,440 --> 00:17:25,240
 "so that we don't have to be dispersed."

407
00:17:25,240 --> 00:17:27,240
 God's judgment comes

408
00:17:27,240 --> 00:17:30,040
 and then the very thing they feared happens to them.

409
00:17:30,040 --> 00:17:34,000
 But they are for the first time in the story

410
00:17:34,000 --> 00:17:35,400
 actually obeying.

411
00:17:35,400 --> 00:17:38,640
 They're actually obeying the cultural mandate

412
00:17:38,640 --> 00:17:40,640
 when God said, "Go out to the earth."

413
00:17:40,640 --> 00:17:42,760
 Disperse and fill the earth.

414
00:17:42,760 --> 00:17:45,680
 Finally, they're obeying it,

415
00:17:45,680 --> 00:17:48,320
 but it took the judgment of God.

416
00:17:48,320 --> 00:17:50,640
 And you realize God's judgment on them

417
00:17:50,640 --> 00:17:55,280
 was actually his mercy to get them to obey,

418
00:17:55,280 --> 00:17:57,200
 except it was the long way.

419
00:17:57,200 --> 00:18:00,300
 And then in verse nine, last verse.

420
00:18:00,300 --> 00:18:03,400
 Verse nine, it says, "Therefore," God changes the name.

421
00:18:03,400 --> 00:18:07,720
 It's name, Shinar's name was called Babel

422
00:18:07,720 --> 00:18:11,280
 because the Lord confused the language of all the earth.

423
00:18:11,280 --> 00:18:13,720
 And from there, the Lord dispersed them

424
00:18:13,720 --> 00:18:15,840
 over the face of all the earth.

425
00:18:15,840 --> 00:18:20,400
 So God changes the name of the city from Shinar to Babel,

426
00:18:20,400 --> 00:18:22,480
 which means confusion.

427
00:18:22,480 --> 00:18:24,680
 So Shinar, the place of potential,

428
00:18:24,680 --> 00:18:27,400
 the place of settling, the place of ingenuity

429
00:18:27,400 --> 00:18:30,120
 becomes Babel, the place of confusion,

430
00:18:30,120 --> 00:18:32,800
 the place of wilderness, the place of restlessness

431
00:18:32,800 --> 00:18:34,060
 and lack of calling.

432
00:18:35,280 --> 00:18:38,040
 And I was thinking some of you tonight

433
00:18:38,040 --> 00:18:44,520
 have moved from the land of Shinar to the land of Babel

434
00:18:44,520 --> 00:18:48,440
 over the past few months, years, weeks.

435
00:18:48,440 --> 00:18:50,360
 You used to have ambition for your life.

436
00:18:50,360 --> 00:18:52,180
 You used to have excitement for your life,

437
00:18:52,180 --> 00:18:55,560
 but due to levels of failure and disappointment,

438
00:18:55,560 --> 00:18:58,180
 you find yourself in the land of confusion.

439
00:18:58,180 --> 00:19:03,200
 For many of you, young adult years is the land of confusion.

440
00:19:03,200 --> 00:19:06,120
 You go to your mom's house, you go back to your parents

441
00:19:06,120 --> 00:19:07,360
 and they go, "What are you gonna do with your life?"

442
00:19:07,360 --> 00:19:12,120
 And you're like, "Babel, confusion, I have no idea."

443
00:19:12,120 --> 00:19:14,440
 Right, some of you, you had exciting things happen

444
00:19:14,440 --> 00:19:15,660
 and then you get beat up,

445
00:19:15,660 --> 00:19:17,960
 like life beats you up a little bit.

446
00:19:17,960 --> 00:19:21,040
 You go through a breakup, the job that you wanted,

447
00:19:21,040 --> 00:19:22,480
 you end up getting let go of,

448
00:19:22,480 --> 00:19:24,540
 or it turns out to be something different.

449
00:19:24,540 --> 00:19:27,560
 The friend group, you're like, "Best friends for life,

450
00:19:27,560 --> 00:19:30,760
 "it's us," totally ditch you.

451
00:19:30,760 --> 00:19:33,800
 All the hopes and dreams that you had crumble

452
00:19:33,800 --> 00:19:35,080
 and it's in that place.

453
00:19:35,080 --> 00:19:35,960
 I mean, think about it.

454
00:19:35,960 --> 00:19:38,240
 This is where the people are at the end

455
00:19:38,240 --> 00:19:40,400
 and it's the judgment of God,

456
00:19:40,400 --> 00:19:44,740
 and yet it's his supreme mercy to take them away

457
00:19:44,740 --> 00:19:47,660
 from the very thing that was gonna lead to their destruction

458
00:19:47,660 --> 00:19:52,560
 to actually, for the first time in a long time, obeying God.

459
00:19:52,560 --> 00:19:54,240
 I think some of you came in tonight.

460
00:19:54,240 --> 00:19:56,000
 I don't know why you're here.

461
00:19:56,000 --> 00:19:59,700
 I think some of you are here because you're in Babel, man.

462
00:19:59,700 --> 00:20:03,480
 You're confused, you're hurt, you're disappointed,

463
00:20:03,480 --> 00:20:07,800
 you're distracted, you're disillusioned with life.

464
00:20:07,800 --> 00:20:12,800
 And it's to you that I wanna give three encouragements.

465
00:20:12,800 --> 00:20:15,200
 I wanna give three kind of takeaways,

466
00:20:15,200 --> 00:20:17,720
 encouragements if you find yourself in Babel.

467
00:20:17,720 --> 00:20:20,440
 These are gonna go quick and then we're gonna rock.

468
00:20:20,440 --> 00:20:22,400
 But three encouragements.

469
00:20:22,400 --> 00:20:25,180
 Number one is just from my heart.

470
00:20:25,180 --> 00:20:26,920
 I was gonna do two and then I added a third

471
00:20:26,920 --> 00:20:28,560
 'cause I had to, so we're gonna go quick, Kylan.

472
00:20:28,560 --> 00:20:29,400
 Here we go.

473
00:20:29,400 --> 00:20:31,480
 Number one, the first encouragement

474
00:20:31,480 --> 00:20:34,500
 is to write out a vision for your life.

475
00:20:34,500 --> 00:20:38,220
 Write out a vision for your life.

476
00:20:38,220 --> 00:20:42,760
 I talk to so many young adults these days

477
00:20:42,760 --> 00:20:46,520
 who have no vision for their life, not at all.

478
00:20:46,520 --> 00:20:48,600
 And it sounds like humility.

479
00:20:48,600 --> 00:20:51,280
 I talk to 'em and go, hey man, what's your trajectory?

480
00:20:51,280 --> 00:20:52,120
 Like, what are you on?

481
00:20:52,120 --> 00:20:53,160
 What do you wanna do with your life?

482
00:20:53,160 --> 00:20:55,240
 It's like, man, I don't know.

483
00:20:55,240 --> 00:20:59,640
 I'm just kinda following God, you know, just like who knows.

484
00:20:59,640 --> 00:21:01,960
 And then when you drill down, you realize,

485
00:21:01,960 --> 00:21:04,520
 wow, your life is full of chaos.

486
00:21:04,520 --> 00:21:07,920
 Like, there's so many like relationships you're juggling

487
00:21:07,920 --> 00:21:09,560
 and work you're trying to figure out

488
00:21:09,560 --> 00:21:12,300
 and you're laying at night kinda juggling

489
00:21:12,300 --> 00:21:14,460
 all these thoughts, sometimes having panic attacks

490
00:21:14,460 --> 00:21:15,700
 'cause you don't know what to do

491
00:21:15,700 --> 00:21:17,400
 with all the things in your head.

492
00:21:17,400 --> 00:21:20,780
 And you're just waiting for someone to give you vision.

493
00:21:20,780 --> 00:21:21,960
 You're looking to your boss going,

494
00:21:21,960 --> 00:21:24,220
 man, I wish you would just like give me a direction.

495
00:21:24,220 --> 00:21:25,280
 Like, what am I supposed to do?

496
00:21:25,280 --> 00:21:26,720
 Give me something to do.

497
00:21:26,720 --> 00:21:28,600
 You're looking for a boyfriend or a girlfriend

498
00:21:28,600 --> 00:21:33,360
 or a spouse, a husband, a wife, a mentor

499
00:21:33,360 --> 00:21:36,200
 to come in your life and just tell me what to do.

500
00:21:36,200 --> 00:21:37,880
 I've literally had young adults say,

501
00:21:37,880 --> 00:21:41,000
 I wish someone would just tell me what to do.

502
00:21:41,000 --> 00:21:43,720
 And yet core to the book of Genesis

503
00:21:43,720 --> 00:21:48,720
 is that God wants you to have a vision for your life.

504
00:21:48,720 --> 00:21:51,000
 I remember a few years ago,

505
00:21:51,000 --> 00:21:53,320
 actually right when I got out of college,

506
00:21:53,320 --> 00:21:55,160
 I met with Matt Chandler.

507
00:21:55,160 --> 00:21:57,600
 Matt Chandler, pastor, he's spoken on the stage.

508
00:21:57,600 --> 00:21:58,720
 I met with Matt and I was like,

509
00:21:58,720 --> 00:22:01,480
 Matt, if you could give any advice

510
00:22:01,480 --> 00:22:04,460
 to people in their 20s, what would it be?

511
00:22:04,460 --> 00:22:07,480
 And right off the dome, he was like, oh man, I know.

512
00:22:07,480 --> 00:22:10,720
 Figure out what do you want?

513
00:22:10,720 --> 00:22:12,480
 Ask yourself that question

514
00:22:12,480 --> 00:22:14,960
 and be brutally honest with the answer.

